[SN]TITLE[SN]
What will life look like in 100 years? Scientists predict the future

[SN]FIRST-SENTENCE[SN]
It looks like something out of a movie, but these striking pictures show how we could all be living in 100 years time.

[SN]RESTBODY[SN]
16 February 2016 Last updated at 14:41 GMT
From living in an underwater 'bubble city' to eating 3D-printed restaurant food and travelling in our own personal drones, scientists working for tech company Samsung have predicted how technology could change our lives in future.
The most dramatic changes look to come in not just how we live but where we live, with science opening the door to homes underwater, underground and holidays on the Moon and Mars.
Take a look at some of the scientists' ideas.
